The paper deals with a communication system and analyzes a composite decode-and-forward scheme for the two-way relay channel with a direct link. It discusses the impact of link state on the allocation of power between two distinct techniques, which governs the necessity of each technique in achieving the largest transmission rate region. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.COMM (Communications), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
